summary: Chemical Engineer with research and development background with an eager desire to learn. Excellent communication skills in Portuguese and English, as well as a good knowledge of French. My last job was as an intern at the Production management area of Iguaçu Company of Soluble Coffee, owned by Marubeni Corporation. Before, I was a math tutor for high school students. I have three years of research experience in heterogeneous catalysis at the State University of Maringa (UEM), Brazil, and the University of Amsterdam (UvA), with a scholarship provided by Federal Brazilian Agency for Science and Technology (CNPq).
